{
  "text": "The coefficients c m of Q λ can be expressed in terms of the characters of the symmetric group S r (this is essentially Frobenius-Schur duality), and each nonzero c m will have jm j = t(λ) [CITATION_1] . We will also write S λ [µ] and P ℓ [µ], when convenient.",
